{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"zoological-violety-inganue","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Problem\nThe f482 null-commit-ledger fix (main 6845b8326) added --full-history to resolve_event_commit/resolve_position_commit for correctness. verify_authorship_at_commit resolves each keyring key's added_at/revoked_at POSITION via resolve_event_commit (now --full-history) once per key per in-scope signed event, so the whole-store gate slowed (~57->~66min in CI; >35min local). This is a NEW instance of the O(events x history) class that closed ticket 1cc0 fixed for the LIVE-event path via build_introducing_commit_map; the era-check path was not covered.\n\n## Fix direction\nExtend the single-pass --full-history position->commit map (build_position_commit_map, added in f482) to also serve verify_authorship_at_commit's per-key lookups, making the era check O(1) map hits instead of per-key --full-history git-log subprocesses.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] verify_authorship_at_commit resolves keyring positions via the batched map, not per-key git log.\n- [ ] Whole-store rebar verify-identity runtime <= pre-f482 baseline on the real store.\n- [ ] Same classifications/verdicts (existing gate tests + a perf-safe regression test green).","id":"f9ce-7098-9f17-433e","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"verify-identity era-check perf: batch verify_authorship_at_commit per-key resolution (--full-history regressed it)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784349460540434001,"uuid":"f8e8e7fe-ef85-4243-b8f2-debb633ee0c2"}